# Meet Scheduling

Meet Scheduling is a backend application that helps users create and manage meetings.
The main purpose of this project is to provide APIs for scheduling meetings and managing meeting-related data efficiently.

## Technologies Used

- Java
- Spring Boot
- Spring Data JPA
- Hibernate
- MySQL
- REST API

## Features

- Create meetings
- Manage meeting details
- Update existing meetings
- Delete meetings
- Store meeting information in database
- Fetch meeting details through REST APIs
- CRUD operations for meeting management

## Project Structure

The project follows layered architecture:

Controller Layer  
- Handles API requests and responses

Service Layer  
- Contains business logic

Repository Layer  
- Handles database operations

Entity Layer  
- Represents database tables/models

